RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMAGE OF QUALITY stalked near the back of the field three deep in the early going, started to figure things out lengthening stride going around rivals four wide at the three eighths marker, was behind horses looking for a clear path at the top of the lane, experienced some traffic issues to the wire but fought on gamely to surge late for the hard fought victory down the stretch. LAST MONARCH had a good spot tracking the contesting duo outside, took closer order when asked midway on the turn, bid four wide outside rivals straightening out for the drive, took control while drifting in at the sixteenth pole but could not hold off the late surge by the winner nearing the wire. CHAIRMAN RAINBOW broke in at the start, travelled in midpack on the rail, tracked behind the top two with three furlongs to go, was on hold in hand on the fence two furlongs from the wire, had clear running room inside at the top of the lane and determinedly finished up the fence to capture third money. JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE was pushed to the rail at the break, assumed command narrowly down the back straight, continued to have a slim lead being hounded outside on the turn, was collared by runners turning for home outside and offered little resistance between foes in upper stretch and faded in the two path at the furlong marker holding on for a minor role. GOLDEN WIND hopped at the break trailing down the backstretch, rallied on the fence midturn, was gaining steadily on the fence in upper stretch, had no room to go at the furlong marker behind runners, shifted out at the sixteenth pole and offered a mild finish late. TODAY settled near the rear four deep down the backstretch, angled to the rail entering the turn advancing inside, was steadied on the fence at the five sixteenths marker, regrouped but was getting out on the turn at the quarter pole, swung five for the drive to the finish and was one paced while drifting out to the wire. BEE BEE THE KING prompted the pace outside down the backside, chased the frontrunner outside throughout the turn, was hard ridden with rivals on either side at the quarter marker vying for the lead and retreated in mid stretch. CORONATION BOY had a slow start to begin, was asked between to get a better position at the half, roused for more midpoint on the turn but to no avail and was empty in the stretch drive.

HANK OLLIE got away well and moved forward, dropped to the rail about the three-quarter content to track inside, was well-positioned in behind the leaders till upper stretch, came out four to five wide for the drive, bid between runners in mid-stretch but was outfinished. MIAH SAID moved forward inside heading into the first turn switching off the rail just past the three-quarters, moved up outside the leader leaving the first turn to press from outside two to three deep, edged closer making a bid at the top of the stretch and with a narrow lead till past the furlong marker, was outkicked. BIG SHOOTER lacked early speed despite moderate encouragement, saved ground along the inside at the rear racing on or just off the rail, began to inch closer on the far turn still saving ground, came out turning into upper stretch, gained steadily moving between rivals at the sixteenth to secure the minor award and continued to make up minor ground on the top trio but too late. STEPHEN B GOOD raced two wide into the first turn mid-division, lost ground on the leading group up the backstretch, began to gain some into upper stretch coming out three to four deep, ran on mildly and needed more. BAIT N SWITCH broke a step slowly and lost the path at the break, settled at the back outside three to four deep, advanced five wide up the backstretch, moved in a bit on the far turn then back out turning for home, could not sustain the effort and evened out in the lane. GLOBAL CHAIRMAN broke a step slowly, was coaxed forward getting caught wide and outside runners into the first turn, was able to shift in on that bend, set the pace shadowed by a rival up the backstretch, was challenged at the top of the stretch, weakened late. SECRET CAMELOT raced outside a foe two to three wide in the back half of the field, moved out leaving the far turn, was unable to menace. DIXIE'S FLATTER briefly chased two to three wide, steadily retreated. TALL BOY JOEL was caught four to five wide around the first turn, dropped back heading into the far turn, faded.

PEMBERLEY was allowed to settle seeing the field into the first turn, advanced smartly on the fence throughout the back straight, was blocked when behind the tiring early leaders inside two furlongs from the finish, swung outside four wide for running room and closed belatedly for second, besting the rest in the end. LADY BREW was under a good hold tracking alone in third watching the top two engage at the half, took up the chase fighting three wide at the quarter marker, could not match strides with the top two turning for home and settled for a clear third crossing the line. NOW IS A BREEZE kept a close eye on the loose frontrunner in the first turn, was content loping along outside at the flank of the leader down the backstretch, was ridden in the two path battling for the lead two furlongs to the finish, could not quicken with others and faded in upper stretch while still holding for a small piece of the prize. MORAL TURPITUDE broke out at the start to travel near the rear into the first turn, could see the field entering the backstretch, offered a mild turn of foot swinging four wide at the quarter pole and had little to show through the stretch drive. WINGS FROM ABOVE took this field inside into the first turn, dictated the pace while prompted outside down the backside, was scrubbed on clinging to the lead at the quarter pole, could not find another gear and backed away on the fence in upper stretch. VIVID VIXEN stalked three wide on the first turn, settled in last outside horses three deep at the half mile marker, could not keep pace on the far turn with rivals, lost touch with the field turning for home and galloped to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIROSA broke sharply to take control from the onset, set the pace alone down the backside, was uncontested making the fractions through the turn, rider looked back for competition at the eighth pole running in hand, was kept to the task just for attention purposes late and cruised in for the effortless victory. GOLDEN CANARY broke out on the break, was in the second flight tracking three deep outside, loomed the only threat four wide in upper stretch and chased the winner in vain to the wire still holding onto the place share in the end. CREVALLE D'ORO travelled inside on the rail in the third flight down the backside, kept pace with the leaders throughout the turn, angled out six wide for the stretch run, was running greenly in the final furlong but finished well being a solid third between runners at the wire. NANTUCKETS DAY stalked close to the back of the field in the beginning, rallied in the seven path widest at the quarter pole, was bumped by inside rival in upper stretch and finished with intent the final furlong to play a minor role in the end. VILLI OLENTO tracked between horses three deep down the backside, slipped back a touch in the two path with three eighths to go, continued to show interest finishing down the stretch and ran on well to the wire in an honest effort. KELLER (IRE) was off slow to begin, stalked in midpack on the rail down the backstretch, made little headway on the fence running through the turn, drifted out in upper stretch driving to the wire to be in the six path at the furlong marker and passed some late to the finish. MAGIC TOKEN ran just off the fence in midfield at the half mile marker, offered a brief run with five sixteenths remaining, angled out for the drive in the six path, bumped outside rival in upper stretch and levelled off in the final eighth. RED SAMURAI was bumped to begin to be close to the back of the pack after the start, made little impression on the turn and could not reach contention driving to the finish. MIRAMICHI broke inwards throwing her head to begin, settled in the third flight outside rival down the backstretch, offered an early move around foes three wide starting at the three eighths marker, was in with a chance for a small share of the prize with three sixteenths to go but stalled in the last furlong. WORLD SHOWCASE tracked the winner on the rail in the beginning, was in range on the fence straightening out for the drive, was asked for more in upper stretch ,no response and stopped on the rail at the furlong marker. SECORD trailed down the backstretch, passed a straggler with three furlongs to go and was not a factor in the stretch run. KOZY KURLIN KITTEN was bumped at the start to be near the back in the early stages, was ridden to keep up on the turn, could see the field turning for home and could not get involved down the lane.

Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Non -Restricted Sweepstakes Of $75,000 Since July 22,2022 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $80,000 (Races Where Entered For $50,000 Or Less Not Consid ered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUPER WATSON was allowed to settle outside in the early going, started a long sustained run around rivals three furlongs to the finish, loomed the threat four deep at the top of the stretch, wore down the leaders to seize control at the sixteenth pole and held safe at the finish. LAST AMERICAN EXIT stalked near the rear on the rail, could not match strides with others quickening at the five sixteenths pole, angled five wide for the drive to the wire and found his best stride late closing gamely to the finish to be second best. SECRET RESERVE had a good position tracking outside four deep, could not maintain position when the winner circled foes midway on the turn, shifted into the rail in upper stretch, weaved his way through traffic at the sixteenth pole and closed in to capture third between horses late. MASON'S GAMBLE waited on the fence trailing the field at the three furlong marker, rallied up the rail in upper stretch, lost path at the furlong pole, shifted outwards and recovered with a strong late run to just miss getting up for third in the end. OUTADORE pressed the issue on the rail down the backside, was shuffled on the fence some into the turn, was in range in the three path behind runners in upper stretch and offered little finish to the wire. MACLEAN'S POSSE was hard held between foes at the half, took up the chase closing in on the frontrunner through the turn, bid outside two wide in upper stretch, was asking for the wire clinging to the lead at the eighth pole and tired in deep stretch. THE MINKSTER took command soon after the start, dictated the pace comfortably on the turn, was collared outside at the top of the lane, battled on the fence until the sixteenth pole and stopped with seventy yards to go.

(Any Maiden Races, And Only Claiming Races And Only Starter Races For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAHIRA'S BLESSING got away alertly and quickly sped clear to set the pace near the inside, reined in the speed a bit on the turn allowing rivals to approach, turned away those and was clear yet again into the stretch, held safe under steady handling. FIRING BULLETS lacked early speed, shifted in, saved ground on the turn on or just off the rail but lacked room inside and in behind rivals under a tight hold from about the three-eighths to the top of the stretch, came out three to four wide at the top of the stretch, moved out further for clearance five to six deep by mid-stretch and kicked on to be clearly second best. CURLIN CANDY got away a step slowly and a bit awkwardly, advanced under some coaxing to move between rivals about the nine-sixteenth and not too far back of the leader, moved out four to five wide turning into upper stretch, evened out late. ROSEBUD'S HOPE settled just off the pace stalking mid-division three to four wide into and on the turn, came out six to seven wide for the drive, ran on and needed more. PROUD SPEAKER chased briefly from outside soon dropping back to settle in outside the trailing group, went four to six wide through the turn, came out nine wide in the stretch and improved position. LADY URUS bobbled just slightly at the start but recovered quickly to get forward position tracking inside rivals and in behind the leader and eventual winner racing off the fence in the two to three path, lacked the needed late kick. SHE MAKES A POINT raced at the back between runners into the turn going three to four deep, needed more. SOUPER PECAN got away well, dropped back off the leaders racing mid-pack outside foes four to five wide into the turn, floated out seven to eight deep turning into the stretch and ran on but needed more. RETAIL THERAPIST saved ground inside but raced one-paced. HAI BOBBI stalked early, was up close and within range three to four wide early on the turn, drifted out leaving that bend and again in upper stretch, faded.
